+# Security Fix: CVE-2026-25087
+
+**Package**: pyarrow 20.0.0
+**Severity**: Medium
+**CVE**: CVE-2026-25087
+
+## Vulnerability
+
+Integer overflow / out-of-bounds read in the Apache Arrow C++ IPC reader
+(`cpp/src/arrow/ipc/reader.cc` and `cpp/src/arrow/type.h`).
+
+Affected code paths:
+- Buffer size calculations in `ArrayLoader::LoadBuffer` could overflow `int64_t`
+- Variadic buffer counts were not validated against available buffers
+- `FileBlock` offsets from the IPC footer were not bounds-checked
+
+## Fix
+
+The following changes were applied to the Apache Arrow C++ source at tag
+`apache-arrow-20.0.0` during the rootio native build:
+
+- Added `SafeSumInt64()` overflow-safe addition helper
+- Added `has_variadic_buffers()` type predicate and variadic buffer count cap
+- Added `FileBlock` offset/size overflow validation in `FileBlockFromFlatbuffer`
+- Added `GetVariadicCount` bounds validation
+
+Patch source: `build/CVE-2026-25087.patch` in `hooks/pypi/pyarrow/20.0.0/`
+Applied to: `https://github.com/apache/arrow.git` at `apache-arrow-20.0.0`
+
+## References
+
+- https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2026-25087
